<subSubSection id="FE01BA14104FCADB09CF41FAFB4605A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph id="45F382578C39859C0E2C2039B260628A" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D882624505840DB2D0661CE64615273" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
The holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="E0A1651AC50DE33634494ECA106CD9EE" genus="D." lsidName="D. pusillum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis id="A216121C297A3E6B43372A5D699671C3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears a handwritten protologue by 
<normalizedToken id="6F08D3282D3F3FA4E90A3B6E23A17D55" originalValue="Labillardière">Labillardiere</normalizedToken>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="024A0313C841852C6372D84D70B9939A" author="Munz, PA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Arnold Arboretum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="159 - 202" refId="B31" refString="Munz, PA, 1967a. A synopsis of the Asian species of Consolida (Ranunculaceae). Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 48: 159 - 202" title="A synopsis of the Asian species of Consolida (Ranunculaceae)." volume="48" year="1967 a">Munz (1967a)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that he saw an isotype of 
<taxonomicName id="8B692244AF7949C48A79739482B78681" genus="D." lsidName="D. pusillum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis id="6BE56EB06505EAB8A9007E2A53309E2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at K (obviously K000692380), but it is not clear whether this specimen belongs to the type collection or not.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="191FB048FC8EEAD31C9AB8905F1BE7E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
As explained by 
<bibRefCitation id="C4EDE513B23288F8349EED9CB26AD706" author="Chowdhuri, PK" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="403 - 425" refId="B9" refString="Chowdhuri, PK, Davis, PH, Hossain, M, 1958. Materials for a Flora of Turkey, III.: Ranunculaceae, I. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 22 (4): 403 - 425" title="Materials for a Flora of Turkey, III.: Ranunculaceae, I." volume="22" year="1958">Chowdhuri et al. (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, when dealing with 
<taxonomicName id="A1BB979B3C5F9A32AC5666CE417B9763" genus="D." lsidName="D. oliganthum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="oliganthum">
<emphasis id="6616AE675E271BE9C52E60E43D6FEEAB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. oliganthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<normalizedToken id="963BF201377480F27FC2CA189F2206AF" originalValue="Haussknecht’s">Haussknecht's</normalizedToken>
gathering housed at G and K is a mixed collection of 
<taxonomicName id="9A11E274D6C4585144DD1D6A53509DA9" genus="D." lsidName="D. hellesponticum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="hellesponticum">
<emphasis id="0F66C4D7D17FC78D827C68F73E1AEE84" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. hellesponticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="356A92388BCE3EDDD1A4F6B030B26766" genus="D." lsidName="D. oliganthum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="oliganthum">
<emphasis id="77E733F986E2B31FBB0E28E8198EC06B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. oliganthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the Boissier herbarium, the folder of 
<taxonomicName id="7520ADA0982E543F67F4D5FF9772223A" genus="D." lsidName="D. oliganthum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="oliganthum">
<emphasis id="6E838F80BE2F2642A9063C5A39AA72BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. oliganthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains two sheets, one with 
<taxonomicName id="7443B71F6CC11934BE8EBA5D9F7B5D57" genus="D." lsidName="D. hellesponticum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="hellesponticum">
<emphasis id="51777BEA5006A14E69F10121071C0DF4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. hellesponticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(G00788351), which bears the original label, and the other one with 
<taxonomicName id="B7465443FF4B04078DF339FA1D33C5D0" genus="D." lsidName="D. oliganthum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="oliganthum">
<emphasis id="FABE939FC94C2C3C07D36C7F027EA0CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. oliganthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(G00788351a), both annotated in 1956 by M. Hossain, one of the co-authors with P. K. Chowdhuri and P. H. Davis. At G, K and P duplicates also contain both species. We complete the first step of lectotypification by 
<bibRefCitation id="297E8514CB9C06A0CF30A96C7269BD3D" author="Chowdhuri, PK" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="403 - 425" refId="B9" refString="Chowdhuri, PK, Davis, PH, Hossain, M, 1958. Materials for a Flora of Turkey, III.: Ranunculaceae, I. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 22 (4): 403 - 425" title="Materials for a Flora of Turkey, III.: Ranunculaceae, I." volume="22" year="1958">Chowdhuri et al. (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, who indicated G and K simultaneously in designating the specimen on the sheet G00788351a at G-BOIS as the second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
